history.content: Definitely take math 54, 53.  For SWE, most of MATH/STAT upper divs are unnecessary.  CS 189 is important and 127/126 can be helpful but they are not really math classes.

Hi, I'm a current sophomore who has only recently realized the importance of math/stats classes even within CS. Math/stats wise, I've taken data8/stat88, CS70 and am taking Math 54 right now. I plan on taking math 53 and stat 140 next semester and then the semester after 189/127 and then potentially math 110 senior year. I was wondering what others thought were the most important math/stats classes to take, especially in the context of SWE, since I don't think I will pursue ML (am just interested in it).

edit: sorry if this has been posted before, i can't seem to find it
